# GitHub repo 2 SSH key (foundersof404)

The second SSH key is for **[foundersof404](https://github.com/foundersof404/)**, not `nexttmind`.

When the user says **push to repo 2**, **push repo 2**, or similar:

1. Use SSH host alias `github.com-repo2` (NOT `github.com`, `github.com-nexttmind`, or `github.com-tidl`).
2. Key file: `~/.ssh/id_ed25519_github_repo2`
3. Default remote: `git@github.com-repo2:foundersof404/tidl.git` (already configured as `repo2`)
4. Never use nexttmind keys (`id_ed25519_github_deploy`, `tidl_deploy_mhmd_al_asher`) for repo 2
5. Never push to `nexttmind/*` with the repo2 key unless the user explicitly asks

## Setup reminder

- Account: [foundersof404](https://github.com/foundersof404/)
- Repo: [foundersof404/tidl](https://github.com/foundersof404/tidl)
- Public key must stay on that account/repo for `github.com-repo2` auth
- Ask if they want a different REPO under `foundersof404`. Do not invent it.

## Quick push pattern

```powershell
git push repo2 HEAD
```
